[I] A package management framework for the Ruby programming language

[T] Its a way to package Ruby libraries/applications for distribution, its a
[T] distribution manager, its a package manager. RubyGems brings to the world
[T] of Ruby a very valuable capability--the ability to manage concurrent
[T] versions of libraries and dependencies between those libraries.

[U] https://www.rubygems.org/

[A] Jim Weirich, Richard Kilmer, Chad Fowler
